    <stitle>10 SPEED TRANSMISSIONS EATON RTLO SERIES - REMOVE - SHIFTER HOUSING</stitle>
    <svcsection/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="remove" graphiccount="3">
        <title>SHIFTER HOUSING</title>
        <para>For models equipped with an oil pump and cooler assemblies, make sure to disconnect the lube line
            connected to the shifter housing.
        </para>
        <para>There are two (2) sizes of bolts. The 1-1/2" bolts are used with the lifting eyes. Note their location.
        </para>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the retaining bolts from the shifter housing flange (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301716" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301716" filename="../figg13/g1301716.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 16. Shifter Housing Bolts</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the nut and washer from the alignment stud (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301716">Figure 16</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">To break the gasket seal, jar the shifter housing.</para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the shifter housing (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301717" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301717" filename="../figg13/g1301717.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 17. Remove Shifter Housing</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the gasket and clean all mounting surfaces of gasket material (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301717">Figure 17</hotlnk>).
            </para>
        </step1>
        <step1>
            <para count="1">Remove the two (2) sets of tension springs, balls, and anti-rotating pins from the housing
                bores (
                <hotlnk xrefid="f1301718">Figure 18</hotlnk>).
            </para>
            <figure id="f1301718" figsize="col-wide">
                <graphic id="g1301718" filename="../figg13/g1301718.webp" type="webp"/>
                <caption>Figure 18. Remove Tension Springs</caption>
            </figure>
        </step1>
    </svcproc>
